Looking back, PRINT ends with T, so the feedback symbol for the last letter should be ✓ if it matched.

That would be contradictory.  
Hence the only consistent reading is that the feedback symbol for the last letter of PRINT was actually ✓, i.e. T is in position 5, and the symbol (-) applied to N.

- Ends with T.  
- N is not in position 4.  

Looks good.
